Instance Methods and Static Methods in Java: 

Instance methods are bound to object. 
Instance methods are not declared with static keyword.
Instance methods can access instance variables and static varaibles. 
Instance methods can access other instance methods and static methods.
Instance methods can have this keyword.
Instance methods are called via object.


Static methods are bound to class.
Static methods are declared with static keyword.
Static methods can only access static varaibles.
Static methods can only access other static methods. 
Static methods cannot have this keyword. 
Static methods are called via class.